    <h1>Aashni Shah</h1>
    <!-- <p class="lead">Always doing what she enjoys...</p> -->


    <p clas="lead">Aashni studies <a href="http://web.cs.toronto.edu/" target="_blank">Computer Science</a> at the <a href="http://www.utoronto.ca/" target="_blank">University of Toronto</a>. Originally from Kenya, she moved to Toronto and has become an active member in both UofT and the Toronto tech scene. A former <a href="http://cssu.ca/" target="_blank">Computer Science Student Union</a> president, a member of the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/UWomenCS?fref=ts" target="_blank">Undergraduate Women in Computer Science</a> group, and an organizer for various events, she has spoken at conferences highlighting hackathons and Women’s Empowerment. Aashni founded the first Collegiate hackathon in Canada, <a href="http://www.uofthacks.com" target="_blank">UofTHacks</a>, and has since enjoyed watching hackathons evolve and grow. Aashni also enjoys <a href="http://blog.aashni.me">writing</a> about her experiences at different tech events, and has interned at companies in Jakarta, Nairobi, Seattle and Toronto.

